If nothing changed then BTS wouldn't have gotten this far.
At some point in the past(around 2016-2017), when BTS began to gain notice in the US there was a talk about them writing and singing English songs. Many ARMYs were opposed and said that BTS didn't have to do it because they're a Kpop group so they should sing in Korean. I remember someone even saying that "RM said that it's not easy to write and sing English songs" that would be favourable to the West.
Annoyed as I was, I answered back saying that if they only had to sing Kpop songs then why would Kpop even bother learning Nihongo to sing and release albums in Japan?! 
BTS changed. They evolved as time passed by. They became better than they were before. I always believed that someday they'll be singing English songs and here we are now~ 
Despite the fact that I stopped being active in the Kpop scene since 2018, I'm still proud of myself that I never doubted them one bit. 
As for ARMY, unfortunately they've garnered more hate than love... I can't help but miss the peaceful and lovable ARMY fandom.
